TO ALL TO WHOM THESE PRESENTS MAY COME GREETINGS

WHEREAS, the Convention relating to International Exhibition was signed at Paris on 22 November, 1928, and supplemented by the Protocols of 10 May, 1948, 16 November, 1996, 30 November, 1972 and the

Amendment of 24 June, 1982 and the Amendment of 31 May, 1988;

AND WHEREAS, Article 35 of the said Convention provides, inter alia, that the same shall be open for accession by any State which is a

Member of the United Nations;

AND WHEREAS, the Commonwealth of The Bahamas is a member of the United Nations;

AND WHEREAS, the Government of the Commonwealth of The

Bahamas having studied the aforesaid Convention and is desirous to become a party to the same;

NOW THEREFORE, the Government of the Commonwealth of The

Bahamas hereby accedes to the aforesaid Convention and undertakes faithfully to abide by all the stipulations therein contained.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I, Janet G. Bostwick, Minister of

Foreign Affairs of the Commonwealth of The Bahamas have hereto set my hand and affixed my seal.
